commit.message:
Fix network writer with new phase tap changer objects.

Signed-off-by: Anne Tilloy <anne.tilloy@rte-france.com>

Non linear shunt are considered as one section shunt.

Signed-off-by: Anne Tilloy <anne.tilloy@rte-france.com>

nodes.bodyText: Maybe log that we only disconnect the shunt but don't do anything else
You can delete these lines (not comment them)
I'm surprised by the end of this statement: what happen if id endsWith LEG1 or LEG3 ?

Are you sure that the g2/b2 (resp. g3/b3) are exported at the good side. Looking to the column names, we have: r, x, g1, g2, b1, b2.
It seems that the side1 is always a read end, and the side2 is the middleBus, so I agree with your implementation, but I'm not totally confident and want to be sure it's OK
I would move the initialization inside the if block.
Why the code is different for the two models: the getMaximumSectionCount is defined in the ShuntCompensator interface, so I guess that points should have the same value.
Is this sufficient to test everything you change in this PR?
